# RSpec Standards

## String Literals
- **Double quotes** everywhere in specs (enforced by RuboCop `Style/StringLiterals`)

## Test Types
- **Models**: `spec/models/` — validations, associations, scopes, instance methods
- **Requests**: `spec/requests/` — use instead of controller specs; test full HTTP cycle
- **Services**: `spec/services/` — unit test the `#call` method
- **Policies**: `spec/policies/` — use `action_policy/rspec` DSL
- **System/E2E**: `spec/system/` — Capybara browser tests for full user journeys
- **Mailers**: `spec/mailers/` — use `have_enqueued_mail` or preview

## FactoryBot
- Always use factories — never `Model.new` or `Model.create` with raw attributes
- Factories in `spec/factories/` — one file per model
- Traits for variations, sequences for unique fields

## Shared Examples & Contexts
- Shared examples in `spec/support/shared/`
- Available contexts: `with_admin_user`, `with_doctor_user`, `with_patient_user`, `with_department_scoped`
- Include via `include_context "with admin user"`

## Auth in Request Specs
- HTML/backoffice: `Devise::Test::IntegrationHelpers` — `sign_in user` (see `spec/rails_helper.rb`)
- API (`type: :request` against `Api::*`): `AuthorizationHelpers#auth_headers(token)` — `get path, headers: auth_headers(api_token.token)`

## RuboCop RSpec (request specs)
- `RSpec/MultipleExpectations` and `RSpec/ExampleLength`: prefer `before { get ... }` then one `it` per expectation (e.g. `it { expect(response).to have_http_status(:ok) }` plus a separate `it` for the body), instead of multiple `expect` lines in a single example.

## Coverage Target
- CI enforces SimpleCov **minimum line coverage 79%** (see `spec/spec_helper.rb`); aim for **>80%** when adding code
- Run with: `COVERAGE=true bin/rspec`
- SimpleCov filters: spec/, config/, db/

## Common Matchers
- `expect(response).to have_http_status(:ok)`
- `expect { action }.to change(Model, :count).by(1)`
- `be_authorized_to(:manage?, record)` (Action Policy)
